      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm a personal trainer putting together some new group programs for a pretty diverse client base. I want to make sure my programming is as evidence-based as possible. From a sports science perspective, are there any documented biological differences in things like muscle fiber composition or overall athletic potential between different racial groups that I should keep in mind when tailoring these workouts?",
